# Components (React + TypeScript + index.css)

## Folder structure

Every component must live in its own folder:

``` src/components/ComponentName/ComponentName.tsx ```

- The component implementation is always in `ComponentName.tsx`.
- Styles are always in `index.css` in the same folder.
- Each component must import its local CSS file at the top:
``` import "./index.css" ```

Do not use:
- CSS Modules
- styled-components
- emotion
- inline styles

Do not import CSS from outside the component folder.

## Hooks folder

Component logic (state, effects, data fetching, event handlers) must be extracted into custom hooks and placed in a `hooks/` subfolder inside the component folder:

```
src/components/ComponentName/
├── ComponentName.tsx
├── index.css
└── hooks/
    └── useComponentLogic.ts
```

- Each hook lives in its own file named after the hook (e.g. `useDebouncedSearch.ts`).
- Hooks are imported in the component file:
  ```ts
  import { useDebouncedSearch } from "./hooks/useDebouncedSearch";
  ```
- The component file should focus on rendering (JSX) — keep business logic in hooks.
- If a component has only trivial state (e.g. a single `useState` toggle), a hooks folder is not required.

## Props definition

Props must be defined in the same file (ComponentName.tsx).
Use type, not interface.
Props must be named ```type ComponentNameProps = {} ```.


## Component declaration

Use named export only (no default export).
Always use arrow function.
Always destructure props in the function parameter.
Always set className = "" as default value.

```tsx
export const ComponentName = ({
  className = "",
}: ComponentNameProps) => {
  return (
    <div className={`component-name ${className}`}>
      ...
    </div>
  );
};
```